Source:  Loughnan Glossary
Author:  LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page:  40
Edition:
Quote:  Head: the act of heading, as: a dog has headed when he has arrived at the far side of the sheep from the starting point. A dog's owner may also may also use the idiom when he will say: 'This dog will head' but also maye be heard to say: 'i can head with him.'
